<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[168,775,764,1397]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,386,1039,1063]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Characteristics.</emphasis>
Annual, dwarf herb, to 
<quantity box="[655,725,1039,1063]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
tall, with angular stems. Leaves 
<quantity box="[498,594,1072,1096]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 mm</quantity>
long, opposite, sessile, with eliptic shape, acute apex and denticulate margin. Flowers: subsessil, 
<quantity box="[470,560,1139,1163]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
long; sepals linearlanceolate with apex acute; corolla white, smaller than the calyx. Fruit: globose capsule, 
<quantity box="[521,581,1206,1230]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long, longitudinal dehiscent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[168,775,764,1397]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,336,1272,1296]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Comments.</emphasis>
This is an infrequent species in the study area. It grows in full sunlight conditions in shallow soils on grassland slopes and at the summit. 
<taxonomicName box="[580,752,1339,1363]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Pelletiera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verna">
<emphasis box="[580,752,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Pelletiera verna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species of its genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[501,611,1372,1396]" name="Argentina" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
